.TH "usb_phy_set_charger_state" 9 "usb_phy_set_charger_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_phy_set_charger_state \- set the USB charger state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_phy_set_charger_state
.BI "(struct usb_phy *usb_phy "  ","
.BI "enum usb_charger_state state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "usb_phy" 12
the USB phy to be used
.IP "state" 12
the new state need to be set for charger
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The usb phy driver can issue this function when the usb phy driver
detected the charger state has been changed, in this case the charger
type should be get from ->\fBcharger_detect\fP.
